      <div class="msgContentFrame">That's exactly how I feel about Ferocity or any damage increasing buff. I've never understood why so many players think these skills are so good. It only makes sense if you're doing a damage burst in order to destroy a mob before it releases its TP skills like cactuars under 50% life and even then your normal weapon skills will get the job done if you've planned ahead properly with Feint backed up. <br /> <br />Bloodbath is total crap in my experience, second wind just keeps getting better as my life total increases (currently healing 240ish), which bloodbath will never reliably match or even come close to. <br /> <br />Agreed with Shock Spikes being great, it will reduce your damage taken as mobs pause for longer before each attack, thus reducing downtime. Though at 20+ you really shouldn't be soloing unless you like the idea of gaining SP at 3-7x slower than a full party can rake it in.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2639653" title="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2639653" rel="external nofollow">http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2639653</a></div></div>
