      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Omena wrote:</div><div class="orig">I never liked Ferocity. Sure, you get to try a big Bloodbathed hit or whatever, but you're spending so much time and stamina setting up a combo that often simply misses and flops unless you've got tons of extra TP or Feint. Even if everything works out, the payoff just isn't that good.  <br /> <br />As for Shock Spikes, I think the first thing anyone doing DoW/DoM should do is get CON to R8 for that because it improves your soloing power tremendously. You'll be able to solo leves much earlier and tackle tough mobs much more safely.</div></div> <br /> <br />Ferocity costs 10% stamina and 1 sec animation, gives 50% damage boost. On something like Doomspike, it shows a rather big difference. If you're afraid it simply misses and flops, you can always Ferocity before Feint, it always work. The thing that is crappy here is Bloodbath, because it consumes 40% stamina, 1 sec animation but gives only 50% of the damage done return to you, unless you have 100 MRD affinity.  <br /> <br />Shock Spikes is useful, no doubt. I don't get it however, even though I did get it back in Beta, was because I just feel like so. <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1807831.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
