      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Khornette wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />1. Lag affect everything, argument of lag is bad to Ferocity applies to everything else, unless you tell me SE specifically make Ferocity lag. Also Ferocity animation is faster than almost every other action, it is about half of the duration of most other animation. <br /></div></div> <br />Yes, lag affects everything. It means using Ferocity is a lot more involved than simply watching a 1 second animation as if it was nothing. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />2. Ferocity give 50% bonus damage on any attack. You said on another post yourself Skewer II give 400% damage, 50%*400% = 200% extra damage, Ferocity + Skewer II = 600% damage. I fail to see how this is not significant. That's 3 Feint mind you, but takes only 1.5 the time it takes for a Feint (Feint animation is twice as long as Ferocity, and as long as Skewer II - Skewer II and Feint have EXACTLY THE SAME animation). <br /></div></div> <br />First of all, Ferocity does not guarantee a 600% damage hit as it can miss and on a successful hit you're still getting &quot;only&quot; 200% from Ferocity itself. The animation doesn't even really matter as you're bottle necked by the global cooldown that exists in all non-TP moves, not the animation which can be canceled out of. Besides, I corrected my numbers as the Skewer line appears to be 300% with Trammel and Feint at 200% as you originally said. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />3. Who said it is common to miss WS? All the test I saw about how DEX have no absolute effect on ACC (leaving it aside that SE did tell us DEX does affect ACC) clearly stated an average of 70% chance to hit. It isn't that bad. <br /></div></div> <br />I think pretty much everyone said it's common to miss WS. I guess you didn't. <br /> <br /><div class="