      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Omena wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Khornette wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />Global CD, what? I'm very sure that Feint -&gt; Thrust takes longer than Ferocity -&gt; Thrust, it's not Global CD, there maybe something very wrong with your connection. I've even had instant Ferocity -&gt; Thrust before, there is no Global CD, the animation dictates the CD. Don't believe me? Taunt/Provoke/Raise Shield etc. all are A LOT faster than a normal attack (ESPECIALLY A NORMAL CRITICAL ATTAC). Have you ever had your Stamina depleted with just Light Thrust by any chance? I saw a lot of people claim that Stamina isn't an issue for themselves, and I think lag must be the reason, it is very easy to deplete the stamina bar because actions are quite fast.</div></div> <br />If there is no global CD, you should be able to use Ferocity, any Surge and Invigorate simultaneously. I don't know about you but I need to wait a set amount of time between each of these actions. Lag makes it difficult to measure the exact time but there is definitely a built-in delay between all non-TP actions. TP moves seem to have a much shorter (or no delay, only lag) and can be animation canceled out of.  <br /> <br />This definitely warrants testing because the UI does not display global cooldowns and even gets the normal cooldowns wrong half of the time, not to mention casting times which are always way off.  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 11th 2010 10:10am by Omena </span></i></div></div> <br /> <br />Yes, there's a CD and that's determined by animation, IT IS NOT GLOBAL i.e different animation has different CD duration, and YES YOU CAN SURGE -&gt; FEROCITY -&gt; BLOODBATH -&gt; WHATEVER VERY QUICK, APPROXIMATELY 2 SEC. Feint -&gt; Whatever on the other hand, is very slow, take 2 sec also, for 2 actions. Know what? I always Surge -&gt; Invigorate -&gt; Thrust in beginning of battle, and that's exactly in the same time as my party mates do Stab -&gt; Stab or whatever. If all your moves have same CD duration, then your connection seriously has gone wrong. If anything, TP moves actually have longer delay, because non TP move like Thrust -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Thrust -&gt; Thrust etc. is close to instantaneous and can drain the whole of my stamina bar in like 6 secs, with Speed Surge and full stamina bar to begin with. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 11th 2010  6:31pm by Khornette </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1807831.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
