      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">Ferocity may have an animation of only 1 second, however, add lag + global cooldown and it easily takes up an extra attack's worth of time.</div></div> <br />Except that the cooldown and the animation overlap, so only the cooldown counts (or only the animation, depending on your perspective). The lag effects how long it takes for the move to trigger after you hit the button, not how much time the move takes away from you when it actually does go off.  Lag puts everything a second behind, but it doesn't prevent you from doing things with those seconds. <br /> <br />Therefore you lose the cooldown time, and that's it.  And, the cooldown time for Ferocity is pretty short.  Lag and cooldown are not reasons to avoid Ferocity. <br /> <br /> </div>
